  "description": [
    "J JWP JH TWO CENTS SCIIANTOjN PA MONDAY MORNING MAY 9 1898 TWO CENTS u N AVAE BATTLE MAY OCCUR ON TUESDAY Seventeen Spanish Warships Are Sighted North of Porto Rico The Governor of San Juan Ordered to Provide Rations for 40000 Spanish Soldiers Preparing for the En gagement That May End the War Copyright 1508 by the Associated Press Cape Haytien Hayti May 8 The Associated Press dispatch boat Dauntless has arrived here According to advices from Martinique the Spanish lleet has not been sighted off the island The governor of San Juan de Porto Rico recently received orders from Madrid to provide rations tor 40000 troops He asked the time of their arrival and got the reply Movements of the Spanish fleet arc kept strictly secret Your question cannot be answered Be prepared It is reported that five Spanish warships were seen off St Thomas on Thursday but they were probably only gunboats from San Juan de Porto Rico scouting SCHLEYS FLEET IS READY TO SAIL The Destination Is Believed to De Key West NEW ORLEANS HAS NOT UT JOINED TUB FLEET THE SOLACE BAILS SOUTHTHE HIQ OLD POINT HOTELS NOT TO BE CONVENT ED INTO HOSPITALS Newport"
